---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About Me" description="Learn more about Gyandeep Singh, a Staff Software Engineer, Healthcare IT Architect, and ESLint TSC Member specializing in distributed systems and developer tooling.">
  <article class="animate-fade-in delay-1">
    
    <!-- Hero / Intro -->
    <section class="about-hero">
      <img src="/assets/images/self.jpg" alt="Gyandeep Singh" class="about-avatar" />
      <div class="about-info">
        <h1>Gyandeep Singh</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Staff Software Engineer &bull; Healthcare IT Architect &bull; Open Source Contributor</p>
        <p class="about-bio">
          Staff Software Engineer with 12+ years of experience transforming complex healthcare challenges into scalable, high-impact technical solutions. My career is defined by building mission-critical platforms—from real-time billing engines processing millions in revenue to ambient clinical intelligence that reduces clinician burnout. I bridge the gap between low-level architectural efficiency and high-level business value, with a deep commitment to developer tooling and open-source contribution.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Milestones / Social Proof Bar -->
    <section class="milestones-bar">
      <div class="milestone-card">
        <div class="milestone-value">12+ Years</div>
        <div class="milestone-label">Engineering Experience</div>
      </div>
      <div class="milestone-card">
        <div class="milestone-value">ESLint TSC</div>
        <div class="milestone-label">Open Source Governance</div>
      </div>
      <div class="milestone-card">
        <div class="milestone-value">Patent Holder</div>
        <div class="milestone-label">NLU &amp; Code Transform</div>
      </div>
      <div class="milestone-card">
        <div class="milestone-value">Distinguished</div>
        <div class="milestone-label">Execution Awards</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="article-content">
      <!-- Pillars of Expertise -->
      <h2>Core Pillars of Expertise</h2>
      <div class="pillars-grid">
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="fas fa-sitemap"></i></div>
          <h3>Architectural Leadership</h3>
          <p>Transitioning complex legacy systems into high-performance, event-driven architectures utilizing Apache Kafka. Focused on system reliability, high availability, PHI data integrity, and strict healthcare compliance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="fas fa-heartbeat"></i></div>
          <h3>Healthcare Tech &amp; Domain</h3>
          <p>Navigating the complex constraints of HIPAA-compliant software engineering. Experienced in clinical workflow optimization, ambient clinical intelligence, and creating tech that helps fight clinician burnout.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="fas fa-terminal"></i></div>
          <h3>Developer Tooling &amp; OSS</h3>
          <p>Steward on the ESLint Technical Steering Committee. Leading open-source governance, steering code quality standards, and maintaining core libraries used daily by millions of developers worldwide.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i></div>
          <h3>Innovation &amp; Patents</h3>
          <p>Active patent holder, specializing in automated code refactoring, structural transformations, and natural language understanding (NLU). Dedicated to solving challenging, unchartered software problems.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Staff Perspective -->
      <h2>Staff-Level Perspective</h2>
      <div class="perspective-grid">
        <div class="perspective-block">
          <h3><i class="fas fa-brain text-accent"></i> Technical Philosophy</h3>
          <p>
            I prioritize long-term maintainability, developer velocity, and robust system design over quick-fix solutions. I believe engineering is about building systems that outlast their creators, choosing simple, elegant architectures to solve complex business problems.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="perspective-block">
          <h3><i class="fas fa-users text-accent"></i> Mentorship &amp; Community</h3>
          <p>
            I believe a Staff Engineer's value is multiplied through others. I focus on growing engineering talent, providing technical mentorship, and serving as a judge for startup competitions (like the MN Cup) to support the broader tech ecosystem.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- Let's Connect CTA -->
      <div class="cta-box">
        <h3>Let's Connect</h3>
        <p>I enjoy discussing distributed systems, healthcare innovation, open source governance, or the future of developer tooling. Let's connect or collaborate!</p>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/gyandeeps" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn-primary">
            <i class="fab fa-linkedin"></i> Connect on LinkedIn
          </a>
          <a href="mailto:gyandeeps@gmail.com" class="btn-secondary">
            <i class="fas fa-envelope"></i> Send an Email
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
